    Package Description
    biscotti.collect
    This package contains interfaces, implementations, and other utilities for working with Collections and Maps.

    • Uses of Navigablelist in biscotti.collect

      Methods in biscotti.collect that return Navigablelist 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.ceiling(E e)
      Returns a view of the least elements in this sorted-list greater than or equal to the given element, or null if there is no such elements.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.descendingList()
      Returns a reverse order view of the elements contained in this sorted-list.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.floor(E e)
      Returns a view of the greatest elements in this sorted-list less than or equal to the given element, or null if there is no such elements.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.headList(E toElement, boolean inclusive)
      Returns a view of the portion of this sorted-list whose elements are less than (or equal to, if inclusive is true) toElement.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.higher(E e)
      Returns a view of the least elements in this sorted-list strictly greater than the given element, or null if there is no such elements.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.lower(E e)
      Returns a view of the greatest elements in this sorted-list strictly less than the given element, or null if there is no such elements.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.subList(E fromElement, boolean fromInclusive, E toElement, boolean toInclusive)
      Returns a view of the portion of this sorted-list whose elements range from fromElement to toElement.
      Navigablelist<E> Navigablelist.tailList(E fromElement, boolean inclusive)
      Returns a view of the portion of this sorted-list whose elements are greater than (or equal to, if inclusive is true) fromElement.
